<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 08 at 8:12PM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT CENTRAL PUSHMATAHA...EASTERN
LATIMER AND CENTRAL LE FLORE COUNTIES THROUGH 900 PM CST...
At 812 PM CST, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles east of Red Oak to Kosoma. Movement was
east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Poteau...                         Clayton...
Talihina...                       Wister...
Howe...                           Red Oak...
Fanshawe...                       Cameron...
Albion...                         Talimena State Park...
Snow...                           Tuskahoma...
Stanley...                        Kiamichi...
Whitesboro...                     Clayton Lake State Park...
Bengal...                         Yanush...
Lake Wister State Park...         Moyers...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
